<item>
            <title>[LU-17416] lctl get_param/list_param option to avoid following symlinks</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17416</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Running &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl get_param -R &apos;&amp;#42;&apos;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on a large filesystem can dump a LOT of duplicate data due to symlinks under &lt;tt&gt;lov.&amp;#42;.target_obds&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;lmv.&amp;#42;.target_obds&lt;/tt&gt; pointing back to the respective &lt;tt&gt;osc.&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;mdc.&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt; trees.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to avoid this duplication with e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;nofollow&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and re-enable it with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;follow&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (depending on which is the default).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="79943">LU-17416</key>
